description: This is a museum for private collection of owl objects. There are thousands of owl-related objects in the museum, including owl-painted screens, plates, ceramics, watches and other handicrafts, as well as owl statues, stamps, etc. The museum was renovated on the basis of residential buildings. It is not large in size, but it is full of warm atmosphere. The museum is very close to Bukchon Hanok Village, but because it is located in a small alley, it is not easy to find. Therefore, there are signs at the entrance of the alley. The outer wall of the museum is full of owls, and the flower pots on the path leading to the museum are also full of cute owl signs of the museum. The more you walk in, the more you will feel It's like entering a fairy tale world. There is a gray owl stone sculpture at the entrance of the museum. It is not big inside. It is a big room with some tables and chairs in the middle. A cup of tea and drinks is provided for visitors who come to visit. Visitors can also freely paint on the spot with the brush provided on the table to draw the owl in their hearts, and can stay in the museum. The exhibition room in the museum is surrounded by cabinets on three walls, which display all kinds of owls, decorations, practical utensils, wall clocks and picture frames. There are paintings, carvings, metal, and wood, as long as you can get anything you want, it can be an owl. If you happen to go to the bathroom, you will find that the small bathroom is also full of owls. About not all places in the photo gallery can take pictures, only limited areas can take pictures, you can sit on a chair and take a photo with the owl. Of course, the staff of the museum will also be very enthusiastic to help tourists who are afraid of taking photos, and also guide tourists to take group photos at the gate. In addition, children who like to collect stamps can also ask the curator to knock on the notebook or white paper they bring as a souvenir.

address: White Cube Seoul, 6 Dosan-daero 45-gil, Gangnam District, Seoul,Korea
description: White Cube Seoul is pleased to present a solo exhibition by Mexican artist Gabriel Orozco, featuring paintings and works on paper originating from his 2021–22 series titled ‘Diario de Plantas’, a collection of notebook studies chronicling his impressions of vegetation and plant life gathered in Tokyo, Acapulco and Mexico City.

address: South Korea, Seoul, Nowon-gu, Wolgye-dong, 466 광운아이스링크
